endpointMIB.name: endpointMIB
endpointMIB.contactinfo: Avaya Customer Services Avaya, Inc. 211 Mt. Airy Road Basking Ridge, NJ 07920 USA WWW: www.avaya.com Tel: +1 908 953 6000
endpointMIB.description: MIB Module for 46xx IP Telephones through Release 2.8 in accordance with 46xx Common Requirements COMPAS 75441, Issue 2.8. Copyright 2006 by Avaya Inc. All rights reserved.

endptMARKET.name: endptMARKET
endptMARKET.description: ID designation. This variable returns a string specifying 'domestic' or 'export'.

endptMODEL.name: endptMODEL
endptMODEL.description: Model identifier. This variable returns a string of up to 8 ASCII characters.

endptMCIPADD.name: endptMCIPADD
endptMCIPADD.description: List of call server addresses. This variable returns a sequence of IP addresses, in dotted-decimal orDNS format and separated by commas, of call server IP addresses available for use.

endptMCIPINUSE.name: endptMCIPINUSE
endptMCIPINUSE.description: Call server address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the call server currently in use.

endptMCPORT.name: endptMCPORT
endptMCPORT.description: Transport layer port number. This variable returns an integer specifying the port number in use by the current call server.

endptPHONESN.name: endptPHONESN
endptPHONESN.description: Housing serial number. This variable returns a string of up to 18 ASCII characters, specifying the serial number on the outside of the endpoint's housing.

endptPWBCC.name: endptPWBCC
endptPWBCC.description: PWB comcode. This variable returns a string of up to 9 numerical characters, specifying the comcode or version number of the printed wiring board of the endpoint.

endptPWBSN.name: endptPWBSN
endptPWBSN.description: PWB serial number. This variable returns a string of up to 18 ASCII characters, specifying the serial number on the endpoint's printed wiring board, or N/A if the board has no serial number.

endptETHERADD.name: endptETHERADD
endptETHERADD.description: MAC address. This variable returns a 6-octet string specifying the endpoint's MAC address.

endptESPEED.name: endptESPEED
endptESPEED.description: Ethernet interface speed. This variable returns a string specifying the endpoint's Ethernet interface speed in Mbps: '100', '10', or '0'.

endptIPADD.name: endptIPADD
endptIPADD.description: IP address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the endpoint's current IP address.

endptDHCPLEASETIME.name: endptDHCPLEASETIME
endptDHCPLEASETIME.description: Duration of IPADD lease. This variable returns an unsigned integer specifying the length of time of the IPADD lease, in seconds as received by DHCP option 51.

endptDHCPLEASERENEW.name: endptDHCPLEASERENEW
endptDHCPLEASERENEW.description: Renewal time of IPADD lease. This variable returns an unsigned integer specifying the length of time at which to renew the IPADD lease, in seconds as received by DHCP option 58.

endptDHCPLEASEREBIND.name: endptDHCPLEASEREBIND
endptDHCPLEASEREBIND.description: Rebind time of IPADD lease. This variable returns an unsigned integer specifying the length of time at which to rebind the IPADD lease, in seconds as received by DHCP option 59.

endptGIPADD.name: endptGIPADD
endptGIPADD.description: List of router addresses. This variable returns a sequence of IP addresses, in dotted-decimal format and separated by commas, of routers available for use.

endptGIPINUSE.name: endptGIPINUSE
endptGIPINUSE.description: Router address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the router currently in use.

endptNETMASK.name: endptNETMASK
endptNETMASK.description: Subnet mask. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the subnet mask currently in use.

endptTFTPDIR.name: endptTFTPDIR
endptTFTPDIR.description: TFTP server path name. This variable returns a string of 0-127 ASCII characters, specifying the path name currently prepended to file names used in TFTP read operations.

endptTFTPSRVR.name: endptTFTPSRVR
endptTFTPSRVR.description: List of TFTP server addresses. This variable returns a sequence of IP addresses, in dotted-decimal orDNS format and separated by commas, of TFTP servers available for use.

endptTFTPINUSE.name: endptTFTPINUSE
endptTFTPINUSE.description: TFTP server address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the TFTP server currently in use (or all zeroes if no server used successfully during initialization).

endptBOOTNAME.name: endptBOOTNAME
endptBOOTNAME.description: Boot code file ID. This variable returns a string specifying the boot code file used to initiate telephone operation.

endptAPPNAME.name: endptAPPNAME
endptAPPNAME.description: Application file ID. This variable returns a string specifying the system-specific application file that should be used for telephone operation.

endptSSON.name: endptSSON
endptSSON.description: Site-specific option number (SSON). This variable returns an integer between 128 and 254 inclusive, specifying the SSON in use. The default is 176.

endptBBURST.name: endptBBURST
endptBBURST.description: Blackburst flag. This variable returns 0 if Blackburst is currently OFF, else 1.

endptHUBSTAT.name: endptHUBSTAT
endptHUBSTAT.description: Hub flag. This variable has been superseded by endptPHY2STAT.

endptDSCPAUD.name: endptDSCPAUD
endptDSCPAUD.description: DSCP for audio. This variable specifies the Differentiated Services Code Point for audio currently in use (between 0 and 63 inclusive).

endptDSCPSIG.name: endptDSCPSIG
endptDSCPSIG.description: DSCP for signaling. This variable specifies the Differentiated Services Code Point for signaling currently in use (between 0 and 63 inclusive).

endptL2Q.name: endptL2Q
endptL2Q.description: 802.1Q framing flag. This variable returns 0 if the Layer 2 802.1Q framing parameter is set to 'auto', 1 if it is set to on/enabled, else 2 for off/disabled.

endptL2QAUD.name: endptL2QAUD
endptL2QAUD.description: Audio priority. This variable returns an integer between 0 and 7 inclusive specifying the current Layer 2 802.1Q audio priority value.

endptL2QSIG.name: endptL2QSIG
endptL2QSIG.description: Signaling priority. This variable returns an integer between 0 and 7 inclusive specifying the current Layer 2 802.1Q signaling priority value.

endptL2QVLAN.name: endptL2QVLAN
endptL2QVLAN.description: Telephone VLAN Identifier. This variable returns an integer between 0 and 4094 inclusive specifying the current Layer 2 802.1Q VLAN Identifier value.

endpt46XXUPGR.name: endpt46XXUPGR
endpt46XXUPGR.description: Upgrade script ID. This variable returns a string of up to 16 ASCII characters specifying the name of the upgrade script retrieved by TFTP after the most recent power-up or reset.

endptDNSSRVR.name: endptDNSSRVR
endptDNSSRVR.description: List of DNS server addresses. This variable returns a sequence of IP addresses, in dotted-decimal format and separated by commas, of DNS servers available for use.

endptDNSINUSE.name: endptDNSINUSE
endptDNSINUSE.description: DNS server address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the DNS server currently in use.

endptDOMAIN.name: endptDOMAIN
endptDOMAIN.description: List of DNS domain labels. This variable returns a sequence of labels, separated by periods, for use as the highest-level domain in resolving DNS names in system values.

endptRTCPMON.name: endptRTCPMON
endptRTCPMON.description: RTCP Monitor address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the RTCP monitor currently in use.

endptPHY2STAT.name: endptPHY2STAT
endptPHY2STAT.description: Secondary Ethernet interface setting. This variable returns 0 if the endpoint's secondary Ethernet interface is currently NOT enabled (or none exists), 1 if the hub is setfor auto-negotiation, 2 for 10Mbps half-duplex, 3 for 10Mbps full-duplex, 4 for 100Mbps half-duplex, and 5 for 100Mbps full-duplex.

endptIRSTAT.name: endptIRSTAT
endptIRSTAT.description: IR Interface flag. This variable returns 0 if the endpoint's IR interface is currently NOT enabled, else 1.

endptSMTPSRVR.name: endptSMTPSRVR
endptSMTPSRVR.description: SMTP server IP addresses. This variable returns a comma-separated list of SMTP server IP addresses available for use, in dotted-decimal or DNS format.

endptDSPVERSION.name: endptDSPVERSION
endptDSPVERSION.description: DSP Version. This variable returns a string of up to 10 characters, that identifies the version of the DSP firmware in the endpoint.

endptLOGSRVR.name: endptLOGSRVR
endptLOGSRVR.description: Event Log server address. This variable returns at most one IP address, in dotted-decimal or DNS format, of the server to be used for event logging. This function is intended for Avaya use, in debugging if necessary.

endptLOGSTAT.name: endptLOGSTAT
endptLOGSTAT.description: Event Log flag. This variable returns 0 if the endpoint's event logging capability is currently NOT enabled, else 1. This function is intended for Avaya use, in debugging if necessary.

endptAGCHAND.name: endptAGCHAND
endptAGCHAND.description: Handset AGC status. This variable returns 1 if the endpoint's handset Automatic Gain Control capability is currently enabled, else 0.

endptAGCHEAD.name: endptAGCHEAD
endptAGCHEAD.description: Headset AGC status. This variable returns 1 if the endpoint's headset Automatic Gain Control capability is currently enabled, else 0.

endptPHY1STAT.name: endptPHY1STAT
endptPHY1STAT.description: Ethernet line interface status. This variable returns 0 if the endpoint's Ethernet line interface is currently NOT enabled, 1 if the Ethernet line interface is currently for auto-negotiation, 2 for 10Mbps half-duplex, 3 for 10Mbps full-duplex, 4 for 100Mbps half-duplex, and 5 for 100Mbps full-duplex.

endptL2QSTAT.name: endptL2QSTAT
endptL2QSTAT.description: 802.1Q tagging flag. This variable returns 0 if the Layer 2 802.1Q tagging parameter is currently OFF, else 1.

endptVLANTEST.name: endptVLANTEST
endptVLANTEST.description: VLAN pause parameter. This variable returns the number of seconds for the endpoint to wait for a DHCPOFFER message when using a non-zero VLAN ID. Valid values are integers from 0 to 999 inclusive.

endptPHONECC.name: endptPHONECC
endptPHONECC.description: Phone comcode. This variable returns a string of up to 9 numerical characters, specifying the comcode of the endpoint itself.

endptVLANLIST.name: endptVLANLIST
endptVLANLIST.description: VLAN ID list. This variable returns a list of zero or more VLAN IDs.

endptAGCSPKR.name: endptAGCSPKR
endptAGCSPKR.description: Speakerphone AGC status. This variable returns 1 if the endpoint's speakerphone Automatic Gain Control capability is currently enabled, else 0.

endptHTTPSRVR.name: endptHTTPSRVR
endptHTTPSRVR.description: HTTP server IP addresses. This variable returns a comma-separated list of HTTP server IP addresses available for use, in dotted-decimal or DNS format.

endptHTTPDIR.name: endptHTTPDIR
endptHTTPDIR.description: HTTP server Directory. This variable returns the path used in formation of the URI for HTTP GET operations.

endptHTTPPORT.name: endptHTTPPORT
endptHTTPPORT.description: HTTP TCP port number. This variable returns the TCP port number used by HTTP during initialization.

endptHTTPUSED.name: endptHTTPUSED
endptHTTPUSED.description: HTTP initialization server IP address. This variable returns a 4-octet IP address for the HTTP server used during initialization (all zeroes if no server successfully used during initialization).

endptPROCSTAT.name: endptPROCSTAT
endptPROCSTAT.description: Local Procedure flag. This variable returns 0 if Local Procedures are currently allowed for this telephone, else 1.

endptPROCPSWD.name: endptPROCPSWD
endptPROCPSWD.description: Local Procedure Password. This variable returns 0 if the Local Procedure Password is null, else 1.

endptSIG.name: endptSIG
endptSIG.description: Signaling protocol download flag. This variable returns the integer corresponding to the current signaling protocol.

endptGROUP.name: endptGROUP
endptGROUP.description: Group identifier. This variable returns the integer corresponding to the current group identifier.

endptSNMPADD.name: endptSNMPADD
endptSNMPADD.description: SNMP source addresses. This variable returns one or more allowable source IP addresses for SNMP queries, in dotted decimal or DNS format.

endptCODESRVR.name: endptCODESRVR
endptCODESRVR.description: HTTP server addresses. This variable returns zero or more HTTP server addresses for software download, in dotted decimal or DNS format.

endptCODEUSED.name: endptCODEUSED
endptCODEUSED.description: HTTP server address used. This variable returns the HTTP server address from CODESRVR used, if any, during initialization, or all zeroes if no HTTP server was used.

endptSTATIC.name: endptSTATIC
endptSTATIC.description: Static programming override flag. This variable returns the integer corresponding to the current level of override permissions for static programming.

endptTLSSRVR.name: endptTLSSRVR
endptTLSSRVR.description: TLS server addresses. This variable returns zero or more Transport Layer Security server addresses for software download, in dotted decimal or DNS format.

endptTLSUSED.name: endptTLSUSED
endptTLSUSED.description: TLS server address used. This variable returns the TLS server address from TLSSRVR used, if any, during initialization, or all zeroes if no TLS server was used.

endptCNAPORT.name: endptCNAPORT
endptCNAPORT.description: Chatter server port. This variable returns the Chatter server registration transport-layer port number (from 0 to 65535; default is 8888).

endptCNASRVR.name: endptCNASRVR
endptCNASRVR.description: CNA server addresses. This variable returns zero or more Chatter server addresses for network analysis, in dotted decimal or DNS format.

endptDSTOFFSET.name: endptDSTOFFSET
endptDSTOFFSET.description: Daylight Savings Time Offset. This variable returns the offset in local time for Daylight Savings Time. Currently used in SIP phones.

endptDSTSTART.name: endptDSTSTART
endptDSTSTART.description: Daylight Savings Time Start. This variable returns the first day or date Daylight Savings Time is effective. Currently used in SIP phones.

endptDSTSTOP.name: endptDSTSTOP
endptDSTSTOP.description: Daylight Savings Time Stop. This variable returns the first day or date after Daylight Savings Time is over. Currently used in SIP phones.

endptGMTOFFSET.name: endptGMTOFFSET
endptGMTOFFSET.description: Greenwich Mean Time Offset. This variable returns the offset in local time for Greenwich Mean Time. Currently used in SIP phones.

endptSNTPSRVR.name: endptSNTPSRVR
endptSNTPSRVR.description: SNTP server addresses. This variable returns zero or more SNTP server addresses for obtaining time data, in dotted decimal or DNS format. Currently used in SIP phones.

endptBAKLIGHTOFF.name: endptBAKLIGHTOFF
endptBAKLIGHTOFF.description: Backlight idle timer setting. This variable returns the number of minutes of idle time, after which the telephone backlightis turned off. Range is 0-999, with a default of 120. Used in phones with backlit displays.

endptDOT1X.name: endptDOT1X
endptDOT1X.description: Current value for 802.1X handling. This variable returns 0 if the telephone supports unicast Supplicant operation only, with PAE multicast pass-through without proxy Logoff, 1 if the same as 0 but with proxy Logoff, and 2 if Unicast both unicast or Multicast Supplicant operation, without PAE multicast pass- through, is supported. The default is 0.

endptAUDIOENV.name: endptAUDIOENV
endptAUDIOENV.description: Audio environment selection index. This variable returns the current setting from the audio environment table (from 0 to 107, default is 0).

endptAUDIOSTHD.name: endptAUDIOSTHD
endptAUDIOSTHD.description: Audio headset sidetone setting. This variable returns the current setting (0, 1, or 2; default is 0).

endptAUDIOSTHS.name: endptAUDIOSTHS
endptAUDIOSTHS.description: Audio handset sidetone setting. This variable returns the current setting (0, 1, or 2; default is 0).

endptDHCPINUSE.name: endptDHCPINUSE
endptDHCPINUSE.description: DHCP server address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the DHCP server from which the telephone's IP address was obtained (or all zeroes if the telephone was statically addressed).

endptDHCPLEASEEXP.name: endptDHCPLEASEEXP
endptDHCPLEASEEXP.description: Remaining time of IPADD lease. This variable returns an unsigned integer specifying the length of time in seconds until the expiration of the IP address lease, or 0 if the lease has expired.

endptDHCPSTD.name: endptDHCPSTD
endptDHCPSTD.description: DHCP lease violation flag. This variable returns 1 if the telephone is not allowed to use the IP address after its lease has expired, or else 0 if the telephone is allowed to continue operating after the IP address lease has expired.).

endptDHCPT1REM.name: endptDHCPT1REM
endptDHCPT1REM.description: Remaining time until IP address lease renewal. This variable returns an unsigned integer specifying the length of time in seconds until the start of the IP address lease renewal, or 0 if the lease has expired.

endptDHCPT2REM.name: endptDHCPT2REM
endptDHCPT2REM.description: Remaining time until IP address lease renewal. This variable returns an unsigned integer specifying the length of time in seconds until the start of the IP address lease rebindingl, or 0 if the lease has expired.

endptICMPDU.name: endptICMPDU
endptICMPDU.description: ICMP Destination support setting. This variable returns 2 if the telephone transmits Destination Unreachable messages with code 2 if the designated transport protocol is not supported AND also if the telephone transmits Destination Unreachable messages with code 3 if a closed UD/TCP port is designated. This variable returns 1 if the telephone only transmits Destination Unreachable messages with code 3 if a closed UD/TCP port is designated. This variable returns 0 if the telephone does not transmit Destination Unreachable messages.

endptICMPRED.name: endptICMPRED
endptICMPRED.description: ICMP Redirect support setting. This variable returns 1 if the telephone supports received Redirect messages as specified in RFC 1122, Sections 3.2.2.2 and 3.3.1.2, or 0 if the telephone does not provide this support.

endptSSONCONTENT.name: endptSSONCONTENT
endptSSONCONTENT.description: Contents of DHCP Site Specific Option Number. This variable returns the data portion of the DHCP SSON as designated by endptNVSSON.

endptBRURI.name: endptBRURI
endptBRURI.description: Backup and restore URI. This variable returns a string specifying the URI used for backup and restore files.

endptNVMCIPADD.name: endptNVMCIPADD
endptNVMCIPADD.description: IP address of call server stored in Non-Volatile Memory (NVM). This variable returns a 4-octet string or DNS string. Default is AvayaCallServer.

endptNVMCPORT.name: endptNVMCPORT
endptNVMCPORT.description: NVM Transport layer port number. This variable returns an integer specifying the call server port number stored in NVM.

endptNVIPADD.name: endptNVIPADD
endptNVIPADD.description: NVM IP address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the endpoint's IP address stored in NVM.

endptNVGIPADD.name: endptNVGIPADD
endptNVGIPADD.description: NVM Router address. This variable returns a 4- octet string specifying the IP address of the router as stored in NVM.

endptNVNETMASK.name: endptNVNETMASK
endptNVNETMASK.description: NVM Subnet mask. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the subnet mask as stored in NVM.

endptNVTFTPSRVR.name: endptNVTFTPSRVR
endptNVTFTPSRVR.description: NVM TFTP server address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the file server as stored in NVM. The default is AvayaTFTPserver.

endptNVSSON.name: endptNVSSON
endptNVSSON.description: NVM Site-specific option number. This variable returns an integer between 128 and 254 inclusive, specifying the SSON stored in NVM. The default is 176.

endptNVBBURST.name: endptNVBBURST
endptNVBBURST.description: NVM Blackburst flag. This variable returns 0 if the Blackburst parameter in NVM is OFF, else 1.

endptNVHUBSTAT.name: endptNVHUBSTAT
endptNVHUBSTAT.description: NVM Hub flag. This variable has been superseded by endptNVPHY2STAT.

endptNVDSCPAUD.name: endptNVDSCPAUD
endptNVDSCPAUD.description: NVM DSCP for audio. This variable specifies the Differentiated Services Code Point for audio stored in NVM (integer between 0 and 63 inclusive).

endptNVDSCPSIG.name: endptNVDSCPSIG
endptNVDSCPSIG.description: NVM DSCP for signaling. This variable specifies the Differentiated Services Code Point for signaling stored in NVM (integer between 0 and 63 inclusive).

endptNVL2Q.name: endptNVL2Q
endptNVL2Q.description: NVM 802.1Q flag. This variable returns 0 if the Layer 2 802.1Q framing parameter in NVM is set to 'auto', 1 if it is set to on/enabled, else 2 for off/disabled.

endptNVL2QAUD.name: endptNVL2QAUD
endptNVL2QAUD.description: NVM Audio priority. This variable returns an integer between 0 and 7 inclusive specifying the Layer 2 802.1Q audio priority value stored in NVM.

endptNVL2QSIG.name: endptNVL2QSIG
endptNVL2QSIG.description: NVM Signaling priority. This variable returns an integer between 0 and 7 inclusive specifying the Layer 2 802.1Q signaling priority value stored in NVM.

endptNVL2QVLAN.name: endptNVL2QVLAN
endptNVL2QVLAN.description: NVM VLAN Identifier. This variable returns an integer between 0 and 4094 inclusive specifying the Layer 2 802.1Q VLAN Identifier value stored in NVM.

endptNVPHY2STAT.name: endptNVPHY2STAT
endptNVPHY2STAT.description: NVM Secondary Ethernet interface setting. This variable returns 0 if the endpoint's secondary Ethernet interface in NVM is currently NOT enabled(or none exists), 1 if the hub is set for auto-negotiation, 2 for 10Mbps half-duplex, 3 for 10Mbps full-duplex, 4 for 100Mbps half-duplex, and 5 for 100Mbps full-duplex.

endptNVLOGSTAT.name: endptNVLOGSTAT
endptNVLOGSTAT.description: NVM Event Log flag. This variable returns 0 if the endpoint's event logging capability in NVM is currently NOT enabled, else 1.

endptNVAGCHAND.name: endptNVAGCHAND
endptNVAGCHAND.description: NVM Handset AGC status. This variable returns 1 if the endpoint's handset Automatic Gain Control capability in NVM is currently enabled, else 0.

endptNVAGCHEAD.name: endptNVAGCHEAD
endptNVAGCHEAD.description: NVM Headset AGC status. This variable returns 1 if the endpoint's headset Automatic Gain Control capability in NVM is currently enabled, else 0.

endptNVIRSTAT.name: endptNVIRSTAT
endptNVIRSTAT.description: NVM IR Interface flag. This variable returns 0 if the endpoint's IR interface capability in NVM is currently NOT enabled, else 1.

endptNVPHY1STAT.name: endptNVPHY1STAT
endptNVPHY1STAT.description: NVM Ethernet line interface status. This variable returns 0 if the endpoint's Ethernet line interface in NVM iscurrently NOT enabled, 1 if the Ethernet line interface in NVM is currently for auto-negotiation, 2 for 10Mbps half-duplex, 3 for 10Mbps full-duplex, 4 for 100Mbps half-duplex, and 5 for 100Mbps full-duplex.

endptNVVLANTEST.name: endptNVVLANTEST
endptNVVLANTEST.description: NVM VLAN pause parameter. This variable returns the number of seconds stored in NVM for the endppoint to wait for a DHCPOFFER message when using a non-zero VLAN ID. Valid values are integers from 0 to 999 inclusive.

endptNVVLANLIST.name: endptNVVLANLIST
endptNVVLANLIST.description: NVM VLAN ID list. This variable returns a list of zero or more VLAN IDs in NVM.

endptNVAGCSPKR.name: endptNVAGCSPKR
endptNVAGCSPKR.description: Speakerphone AGC status. This variable returns 1 if the endpoint's speakerphone Automatic Gain Control capability in NVM is currently enabled, else 0.

endptNVHTTPSRVR.name: endptNVHTTPSRVR
endptNVHTTPSRVR.description: NVM HTTP server IP addresses. This variable returns a comma-separated list of HTTP server IP addresses available for use as stored in NVM, in dotted-decimal format.

endptNVAUTH.name: endptNVAUTH
endptNVAUTH.description: Script file authentication flag. This variable returns 1 if the endpoint must authenticate script files, else 0.

endptNVFILESRVR.name: endptNVFILESRVR
endptNVFILESRVR.description: NVM File server address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the file server as stored in NVM.

endptNVALERT.name: endptNVALERT
endptNVALERT.description: Alerting Mode flag. This variable returns 1 if the alerting mode setting in non-volatile memory is enabled, else 0.

endptNVCHADDR.name: endptNVCHADDR
endptNVCHADDR.description: Manually-entered DHCP chaddr value. This variable returns a manually-entered value for the DHCP chaddr field as stored in non-volatile memory, if any. A Hexadecimal value with range of 0 (the default) to 999999.

endptNVCONTRAST.name: endptNVCONTRAST
endptNVCONTRAST.description: Display Contrast setting. This variable returns the value of the display contrast setting in non-volatile memory. Range is 0-15, with 8 the default.

endptUPGRADESCRIPT.name: endptUPGRADESCRIPT
endptUPGRADESCRIPT.description: Script loading status flag. This variable returns '0' if the upgrade script (endpt46XXUPGR) was successfully obtained and interpreted since the last power-up or reset. This variable returns '1' if the upgrade script was successfully obtained and but NOT successfully interpreted since the last power-up or reset. This variable returns '2' if the upgrade script was NOT successfully obtained since the last power-up or reset.

endptAPPINUSE.name: endptAPPINUSE
endptAPPINUSE.description: Application file name. This variable returns the name of the application file in the endpoint.

endptAPPSTAT.name: endptAPPSTAT
endptAPPSTAT.description: Application download flag. This variable returns '0' if the most recent attempt to download and store an application file was successful. This variable returns '1' if the most recent attempt to download an application file was successful but the file was not successfully stored in NVM. This variable returns '2' if the most recent attempt to download an application file was NOT successful.

endptRecentLog.name: endptRecentLog
endptRecentLog.description: Each entry is one of up to 75 syslog event messages added since last reset or power-up, each of which has severity code less than the value of NVLOGLOCAL. Entries are in chronological order, oldest first.

endptRecentLogEntry.name: endptRecentLogEntry
endptRecentLogEntry.description: Each entry is one of up to 75 syslog event messages added since last reset or power-up, each of which has severity code less than the value of NVLOGLOCAL. Entries are in chronological order, oldest first.

endptResetLog.name: endptResetLog
endptResetLog.description: Each entry is one of up to 75 syslog event messages added before the last reset or power-up, each of which has severity code less than the value of NVLOGLOCAL. Entries are in chronological order, oldest first.

endptResetLogEntry.name: endptResetLogEntry
endptResetLogEntry.description: Each entry is one of up to 75 syslog event messages added before the last reset or power-up, each of which has severity code less than the value of NVLOGLOCAL. Entries are in chronological order, oldest first.

endptPORTAUD.name: endptPORTAUD
endptPORTAUD.description: Transport-layer audio port. This variable returns the endpoint's transport layer port number for audio, currently in use.

endptPORTSIG.name: endptPORTSIG
endptPORTSIG.description: Transport-layer signaling port. This variable returns the endpoint's transport layer port number for signaling, currently in use.

endptFEIPADD.name: endptFEIPADD
endptFEIPADD.description: Audio endpoint address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the address of the far-end audio endpoint currently in use.

endptFEPORT.name: endptFEPORT
endptFEPORT.description: Audio endpoint port number. This variable returns the far-end endpoint's transport layer port number for audio, currently in use.

endptCODECR.name: endptCODECR
endptCODECR.description: Receive codec. This variable returns the designation of the Receive codec currently in use.

endptCODECT.name: endptCODECT
endptCODECT.description: Transmit codec. This variable returns the designation of the Transmit codec currently in use.

endptJCPC.name: endptJCPC
endptJCPC.description: Jitter compensation packet count. This variable returns the Jitter compensation packet count currently in use (between 0 and 20, inclusive).

endptTMSEC.name: endptTMSEC
endptTMSEC.description: Transmit buffer fill level. This variable returns the transmit buffer minimum fill level, in msec, currently in use.

endptNVPHONEXT.name: endptNVPHONEXT
endptNVPHONEXT.description: Endpoint's phone extension. This variable returns a text string identifying the endpoint's extension, in free text format. The default value is NULL.

endptL2QBBE.name: endptL2QBBE
endptL2QBBE.description: 802.1Q BBE priority value. This variable returns an integer between 0 and 7 inclusive specifying the far-end endpoint's Layer 2 Better than Best Effort audio priority value.

endptDSCPBBE.name: endptDSCPBBE
endptDSCPBBE.description: DSCP BBE priority value. This variable returns an integer between 0 and 7 inclusive specifying the far-end endpoint's DiffServ Better than Best Effort audio priority value.

endptRTCPCONT.name: endptRTCPCONT
endptRTCPCONT.description: RTCP Control flag. This variable returns 0 if the RTCP control status is off/disabled, else 1.

endptRTCPFLOW.name: endptRTCPFLOW
endptRTCPFLOW.description: RTCP Flowrate. This variable returns an integer between 0 and 65335 inclusive specifying the RTCP flowrate in milliseconds.

endptRSVPCONT.name: endptRSVPCONT
endptRSVPCONT.description: RSVP Control flag. This variable returns 0 if the RSVP control status is off/disabled, else 1.

endptRSVPRFRSH.name: endptRSVPRFRSH
endptRSVPRFRSH.description: RSVP Refresh rate. This variable returns an integer between 0 and 65335 inclusive specifying the RSVP refresh rate in milliseconds.

endptRSVPRTRY.name: endptRSVPRTRY
endptRSVPRTRY.description: RSVP Failed Retry flag. This variable returns 0 if the RSVP Failed Retry Reservation control status is off/disabled, else 1.

endptRSVPPROF.name: endptRSVPPROF
endptRSVPPROF.description: RSVP profile flag. This variable returns 0 if the RSVP profile is guaranteed, else 1 for controlled load.

endptPHNCC.name: endptPHNCC
endptPHNCC.description: Telephone country code. This variable returns 1-3 digits; the administered international country code for the location of the serving call server.

endptPHNDPLENGTH.name: endptPHNDPLENGTH
endptPHNDPLENGTH.description: Telephone dial plan length. This variable returns 1 or 2 digits (3-10); the length of the administered dial plan for the serving call server.

endptPHNIC.name: endptPHNIC
endptPHNIC.description: Telephone international access code. This variable returns 1-4 digits; the digits dialed to access public network international trunks from the serving call server.

endptPHNLD.name: endptPHNLD
endptPHNLD.description: Telephone long distance access code. This variable returns 1 digit or Null; the digit dialed to access public network long distance trunks from the serving call server.

endptPHNLDLENGTH.name: endptPHNLDLENGTH
endptPHNLDLENGTH.description: Length of national telephone number. This variable returns 1 or 2 digits (5-15); the number of digits in the longest possible national telephone number for the location of the serving call server.

endptPHNOL.name: endptPHNOL
endptPHNOL.description: Outside line access code. This variable returns 1 or 2 digits or Null; the digit(s) dialed to access public network local trunks from the serving call server.

endptNTWKAUDIO.name: endptNTWKAUDIO
endptNTWKAUDIO.description: Network audio quality display flag. This variable returns 0 if the Network audio quality display status is off/disabled, else 1. This flag does not apply to the 4610, 4620, or 4630 IP Telephones.

endptENHDIALSTAT.name: endptENHDIALSTAT
endptENHDIALSTAT.description: Enhanced Local Dialing status. This variable returns 0 if the Enhanced Local Dialing status is off/disabled, else 1.

endptRESTORESTAT.name: endptRESTORESTAT
endptRESTORESTAT.description: FTP Backup/restore status. This variable returns 0 if the automatic FTP backup and restore feature status is off/disabled, else 1.

endptFTPUSERSTAT.name: endptFTPUSERSTAT
endptFTPUSERSTAT.description: FTP User permissions status. This variable returns 0 if the user may not change previously-administered FTP server and Directory data, 1 if the user may change or create both FTP server and Directory data, and 2 if the user may only change or create FTP Directory data.

endptRASGkList.name: endptRASGkList
endptRASGkList.description: Each entry is one of up to 30 gatekeeper addresses in dotted-decimal or DNS format, as downloaded from the call server during RAS. Entries are listed in the order received.

endptRASGkEntry.name: endptRASGkEntry
endptRASGkEntry.description: Each entry is one of up to 30 gatekeeper addresses in dotted-decimal or DNS format, as downloaded from the call server during RAS. Entries are listed in the order received.

endptRASGkEntryData.name: endptRASGkEntryData
endptRASGkEntryData.description: Data for an individual RAS-provided Gatekeeper.

endptCIBURL.name: endptCIBURL
endptCIBURL.description: Documentation URL. This variable returns a URL of the directory in which the web-based Customer Information Booklet web pages are located.

endptDIRSRVR.name: endptDIRSRVR
endptDIRSRVR.description: LDAP Server address. This variable returns a the IP address of the LDAP server to be used for the phone's Directoryapplication, in dotted decimal or DNS format.

endptDIRTOPDN.name: endptDIRTOPDN
endptDIRTOPDN.description: Directory Top Name. This variable returns a string specifying the Topmost Distinguished Name in the LDAP Directory to be used for the 4630's Directory application.

endptDIRFULLNAME.name: endptDIRFULLNAME
endptDIRFULLNAME.description: Directory FullName Label. This variable returns a string specifying the LDAP Directory's Full Name Field Label, to be used for the 4630's Directory application.

endptDIRTELNUM.name: endptDIRTELNUM
endptDIRTELNUM.description: Directory Phone Number Label. This variable returns a string specifying the LDAP Directory's Telephone Number Field Label, to be used for the 4630's Directory application.

endptDIRSRCHTIME.name: endptDIRSRCHTIME
endptDIRSRCHTIME.description: Directory Search Duration. This variable returns an integer specifying the maximum number of seconds the LDAP Directory should be searched before reporting completion or failure of the search.

endptDIRSRVRPWD.name: endptDIRSRVRPWD
endptDIRSRVRPWD.description: Directory Access Password. This variable returns a string specifying the password used for accessing the LDAP Directory. The null string is returned if no password has been specified.

endptDIRUSERID.name: endptDIRUSERID
endptDIRUSERID.description: Directory Access User ID. This variable returns a string specifying the User identity used for accessing the LDAP Directory. The null strong is returned if no user ID has been specified.

endptDIRCODING.name: endptDIRCODING
endptDIRCODING.description: Directory Coding Scheme. This variable returns a string specifying the character coding scheme (e.g. ASCII or Latin-1) to be used for LDAP Directory queries.

endptDIRSTAT.name: endptDIRSTAT
endptDIRSTAT.description: Directory Connection Status. This variable returns an integer specifying the result code for the most recent Bind Request sent by the 4630 to the LDAP server.

endptFTPSRVR.name: endptFTPSRVR
endptFTPSRVR.description: FTP Server address. This variable returns the IP address of the FTP server to be used for the phone's file storage and retrieval, in dotted decimal or DNS format.

endptFTPDIR.name: endptFTPDIR
endptFTPDIR.description: FTP Server directory. This variable returns a path name of the directory on the FTP server to be used for the phone's file storage and retrieval.

endptPHNEMERGNUM.name: endptPHNEMERGNUM
endptPHNEMERGNUM.description: Emergency number. This variable returns a string specifying the emergency number to be outpulsed when the user presses the optional Emergency button in the 4630 Speed Dial application.

endptPHNNUMOFCA.name: endptPHNNUMOFCA
endptPHNNUMOFCA.description: Number of Call Appearances. This variable returns the number of Call Appearances downloaded from the DEFINITY during registration to the 4630, 462x and 4610SW.

endptPHNNUMOFFB.name: endptPHNNUMOFFB
endptPHNNUMOFFB.description: Number of Feature Buttons. This variable returns the number of administered Feature Buttons downloaded from the switch during registration to the 4630, 462x and 4610SW.

endptWEBCODING.name: endptWEBCODING
endptWEBCODING.description: Web Coding Scheme. This variable returns a string specifying the character coding scheme (e.g. ASCII or Latin-1) to be used for characters entered on forms on web pages. Used by the 4630 Web application.

endptWEBEXCEPT.name: endptWEBEXCEPT
endptWEBEXCEPT.description: Web Proxy Server Exception List. This variable returns a string specifying a list of one or more HTTP proxy server Exception domains, separated by commas with no intervening spaces, up to 127 total characters. Used by the 4630 Web application.

endptWEBHOME.name: endptWEBHOME
endptWEBHOME.description: Web application URL. This variable returns a URL of the Home page for the 4630 Web application.

endptWEBPORT.name: endptWEBPORT
endptWEBPORT.description: Web application TCP port. This variable returns an integer specifying the TCP port most recently used for the HTTP proxy server. Used by the 4630 Web application.

endptWEBPROXY.name: endptWEBPROXY
endptWEBPROXY.description: Web Proxy Server. This variable returns an IP addresses, in dotted-decimal or DNS format, of an HTTP proxy server. Used by the 4630 Web application.

endptDIRLDAPPORT.name: endptDIRLDAPPORT
endptDIRLDAPPORT.description: LDAP Directory Port. This variable returns the port number for LDAP messages, and has a default value of 389.

endptVMLCODING.name: endptVMLCODING
endptVMLCODING.description: Voice Mail Coding Scheme. This variable returns a string specifying the character coding scheme (e.g. ASCII or Latin-1) to be used for characters entered on forms on the 4630 Voice Mail application.

endptVMLHOME.name: endptVMLHOME
endptVMLHOME.description: Voice Mail application URL. This variable returns a URL of the Home page for the 4630 Voice Mail application.

endptCLACTIVE.name: endptCLACTIVE
endptCLACTIVE.description: Call Log activation flag. This variable returns 0 if the call log status is off/disabled, else 1.

endptWMLCODING.name: endptWMLCODING
endptWMLCODING.description: 4610SW/2x Web Coding Scheme. This variable returns a string specifying the character coding scheme (e.g. ASCII or Latin-1) to be used for characters entered on forms on web pages. Used by the 4610SW/462x Web application.

endptWMLEXCEPT.name: endptWMLEXCEPT
endptWMLEXCEPT.description: 4610SW/2x Web Proxy Server Exception List. This variable returns a string specifying a list of one or more HTTP proxy server Exception domains, separated by commas with no intervening spaces, up to 127 total characters. Used by the 4610SW/462x Web application.

endptWMLHOME.name: endptWMLHOME
endptWMLHOME.description: 4610SW/2x Web application URL. This variable returns a URL of the Home page for the 4610SW/462x Web application.

endptWMLPORT.name: endptWMLPORT
endptWMLPORT.description: 4610SW/2x Web application TCP port. This variable returns an integer specifying the TCP port most recently used for the HTTP proxy server. Used by the 4610SW/462x Web application.

endptWMLPROXY.name: endptWMLPROXY
endptWMLPROXY.description: 4610SW/2x Web Proxy Server. This variable returns an IP addresses, in dotted-decimal or DNS format, of an HTTP proxy server. Used by the 4610SW/2x Web application.

endptCTISTAT.name: endptCTISTAT
endptCTISTAT.description: CTI flag. This variable returns 0 if the CTI application is set to off, else 1.

endptCTIUDPPORT.name: endptCTIUDPPORT
endptCTIUDPPORT.description: CTI application UDP port. This variable returns an integer specifying the UDP port most recently used for the UDP listener to receive broadcast messages.

endptSTKSTAT.name: endptSTKSTAT
endptSTKSTAT.description: Stock Ticker flag. This variable returns 0 if the 4630 Stock Ticker application is set to off, else 1.

endptSUBSCRIBELIST.name: endptSUBSCRIBELIST
endptSUBSCRIBELIST.description: 4610SW/2x Web push subscription list. This variable returns a string containing one or more fully qualified URLs to which the phone's Web application subscribes for potential pushed content.

endptTPSLIST.name: endptTPSLIST
endptTPSLIST.description: 4610SW/2x Web Trusted Push Server list. This variable returns a string containing one or more domains and paths in DNS format, used to determine for validation of push requests.

endptWMLIDLETIME.name: endptWMLIDLETIME
endptWMLIDLETIME.description: Web Idle Timer. This variable returns the number of minutes, from 1 to 60 inclusive, of idle activity on the telephone before the Web Idle Timer URI is displayed.

endptWMLIDLEURI.name: endptWMLIDLEURI
endptWMLIDLEURI.description: Web Idle Timer URI. This variable returns the URI of the WML page displayed after the 4610SW/462x Web Idle Timer expires.

endptFKEU.name: endptFKEU
endptFKEU.description: FKEU flag. This variable returns 0 if the Feature Key Expansion Unit is off, disabled, or not present, else 1.

endptFKEUHEALTH.name: endptFKEUHEALTH
endptFKEUHEALTH.description: FKEU flag. This variable returns 1 if the most recent self-test of the Feature Key Expansion Unit or the 4620 failed, else 0.

endptCALLFWDSTAT.name: endptCALLFWDSTAT
endptCALLFWDSTAT.description: Call Forwarding setting. This variable returns the sum of all Call Forwarding permissions. Range is 0 to 7, with 0 as the default.

endptCOVERAGEADDR.name: endptCOVERAGEADDR
endptCOVERAGEADDR.description: Call Coverage Server address. This variable returns the URI to which call coverage is sent; up to 255 characters.

endptDATETIMEFORMAT.name: endptDATETIMEFORMAT
endptDATETIMEFORMAT.description: Date and Time format specification. This variable returns a parameter indicating the desired format for display of date and time. Range is 0 to 3, with 0 as the default.

endptMUSICSRVR.name: endptMUSICSRVR
endptMUSICSRVR.description: List of music server addresses. This variable returns a sequence of IP addresses, in dotted-decimal format and separated by commas, of music servers available for use.

endptMUSICSRVRINUSE.name: endptMUSICSRVRINUSE
endptMUSICSRVRINUSE.description: Music server address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the music server most recently used.

endptMWISRVR.name: endptMWISRVR
endptMWISRVR.description: List of message waiting indicator server addresses. This variable returns a sequence of IP addresses, in dotted-decimal format and separated by commas, of message waiting indicator servers available for use.

endptMWISRVRINUSE.name: endptMWISRVRINUSE
endptMWISRVRINUSE.description: Message waiting indicator server address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the message waiting indicator server most recently used.

endptREGISTERWAIT.name: endptREGISTERWAIT
endptREGISTERWAIT.description: Registration wait interval. This variable returns the number of seconds between attempts to re-register with the current server. Range is 0 to 65535, with 3600 as the default.

endptSIPPROXYSRVR.name: endptSIPPROXYSRVR
endptSIPPROXYSRVR.description: List of SIP Proxy server addresses. This variable returns a sequence of IP addresses, in dotted-decimal format and separated by commas, of SIP Proxy servers available for use.

endptSIPPROXYSRVRINUSE.name: endptSIPPROXYSRVRINUSE
endptSIPPROXYSRVRINUSE.description: SIP Proxy server address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the SIP Proxy server most recently used.

endptSIPREGISTRAR.name: endptSIPREGISTRAR
endptSIPREGISTRAR.description: List of SIP registrar addresses. This variable returns a sequence of IP addresses, in dotted-decimal format and separated by commas, of SIP registrars available for use.

endptSIPREGISTRARINUSE.name: endptSIPREGISTRARINUSE
endptSIPREGISTRARINUSE.description: SIP registrar address. This variable returns a 4-octet string specifying the IP address of the SIP registrar most recently used.

endptSPEAKERSTAT.name: endptSPEAKERSTAT
endptSPEAKERSTAT.description: Speaker setting. This variable returns a parameter indicating the allowed level of speakerphone functionality. Range is 0 to 2, with 2 as the default.

endptSIPPORT.name: endptSIPPORT
endptSIPPORT.description: TCP/UDP port used for SIP messages. This variable returns the current port number used for SIP messaging. The default is 5060.

endptSIPDOMAIN.name: endptSIPDOMAIN
endptSIPDOMAIN.description: SIP registration domain name. This text is used in the Contact header field as part of SIP registration.

endptPHNNUMOFSA.name: endptPHNNUMOFSA
endptPHNNUMOFSA.description: Number of Session Appearances. This variable returns the number of Session Appearances administered for the SIP phone.

endptDIALWAIT.name: endptDIALWAIT
endptDIALWAIT.description: Dialing timeout interval. This variable returns the number of seconds after the user stops dialing, that the telephone waits before automatically dialing the number enterered so far. The range is 0 to 10, and zero seconds means the telephone will wait forever, or until the user presses Send.

endptDIALPLAN.name: endptDIALPLAN
endptDIALPLAN.description: SIP dial plan. This variable returns the administered dial plan, used during manual dialing to allow a call to be initiated without the use of a Send button and without waiting for the expiration of a timeout interval; up to 1000 characters.

endptCALLFWDADDR.name: endptCALLFWDADDR
endptCALLFWDADDR.description: Call Forwarding address. This variable returns the URI to which calls are forwarded; up to 255 characters.

endptCALLFWDDELAY.name: endptCALLFWDDELAY
endptCALLFWDDELAY.description: Call Forwarding delay. This variable returns the number of times the telephone will ring before a call is forwarded, if Call Forwarding on No Answer is selected.
